CC  The aspartate semialdehyde biosynthesis is a two step pathway. [2] The
CC  product of this pathway can be used in the lysine biosynthesis or in
CC  the pathway leading to  homoserine involved in the threonine,
CC  isoleucine and methionine biosynthesis. There are three different
CC  isozymes differed in their sensitivity to regulation by Lys, Met and
CC  Thr in Escherichia coli. [1]
